{
  "texts": [
    "Starting cells for random walks can be sampled either at random or from a user-defined early cell cluster.",
    "We terminate random walks when a predefined maximum number of steps has been performed or when a predefined set of terminal cells has been reached.",
    "By studying multiple random walks, the expected dynamics are revealed.",
    "Random walks, including their start and final cells, can then be visualized in a low-dimensional representation of the data.",
    "Within our framework, random walks are computed efficiently via a parallel implementation."
  ]
}